- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper specifically focuses on complex recurrent neural network architectures, which falls under the subfield of neural computing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for improving accuracy and reducing computational load in prediction tasks, which falls under the broader category of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed method could potentially be applied to sequence prediction tasks in social and information networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed method could also potentially be applied to control systems for prediction tasks.
